{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 17:01:51,037", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task2: ```python\ndef score_candidate_response(response, criteria_weights, keywords):\n    \"\"\"\n    Scores a candidate's interview response based on predefined criteria and keywords.\n\n    Args:\n        response (str): The candidate's interview response text.\n        criteria_weights (dict): A dictionary mapping evaluation criteria to their weights.\n                                  Example: {\"Technical Skills\": 0.25, \"Problem-solving abilities\": 0.20, ...}\n        keywords (dict): A dictionary mapping evaluation criteria to a list of relevant keywords.\n                         Example: {\"Technical Skills\": [\"python\", \"algorithm\", \"data structure\"], \"Problem-solving abilities\": [\"debugging\", \"optimization\", \"testing\"], ...}\n\n    Returns:\n        dict: A dictionary containing the scores for each evaluation criterion and the overall score.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    response = response.lower()\n    scores = {}\n    overall_score = 0\n\n    for criterion, weight in criteria_weights.items():\n        scores[criterion] = 0\n        if criterion in keywords:\n            relevant_keywords = keywords[criterion]\n            keyword_count = 0\n            for keyword in relevant_keywords:\n                if keyword in response:\n                    keyword_count += 1\n            scores[criterion] = keyword_count / len(relevant_keywords) if len(relevant_keywords) > 0 else 0\n        overall_score += scores[criterion] * weight\n\n    scores[\"overall_score\"] = overall_score\n    return scores\n\ndef example_usage():\n    \"\"\"\n    Provides an example of how to use the scoring function.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    example_response = \"I have extensive experience with Python and data structures. I also have experience in debugging and optimizing code.\"\n    example_criteria_weights = {\n        \"Technical Skills\": 0.4,\n        \"Problem-solving abilities\": 0.3,\n        \"Communication skills\": 0.1,\n        \"Experience\": 0.2\n    }\n    example_keywords = {\n        \"Technical Skills\": [\"python\", \"algorithm\", \"data structure\"],\n        \"Problem-solving abilities\": [\"debugging\", \"optimization\", \"testing\"],\n        \"Experience\": [\"years of experience\", \"project\", \"worked on\"]\n    }\n\n    scores = score_candidate_response(example_response, example_criteria_weights, example_keywords)\n    print(scores)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    example_usage()\n```"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 17:01:51,037", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task3: ```python\nimport random\n\ndef generate_technical_questions(job_criteria, candidate_profile):\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate technical interview questions based on job criteria and candidate profile.\n\n    Args:\n        job_criteria (list of str): Key evaluation criteria extracted from the job description.\n        candidate_profile (dict): Candidate resume details including skills, experience, projects.\n\n    Returns:\n        list of str: A customized list of interview questions.\n    \"\"\"\n    questions = []\n\n    # 1. Technical Skills questions\n    if \"Technical Skills\" in job_criteria:\n        for tech in candidate_profile.get(\"skills\", []):\n            questions.append(\n                f\"Can you describe your experience with {tech}? \"\n                \"What were the main challenges and how did you overcome them?\"\n            )\n\n    # 2. Problem-solving / algorithm questions\n    if \"Problem-solving abilities\" in job_criteria:\n        questions.append(\n            \"Describe a complex technical problem you solved. \"\n            \"What was your approach to ensure correctness and efficiency?\"\n        )\n\n    # 3. Experience-based questions\n    if \"Experience\" in job_criteria:\n        for exp in candidate_profile.get(\"work_experience\", []):\n            title = exp.get(\"job_title\", \"your role\")\n            company = exp.get(\"company\", \"your company\")\n            questions.append(\n                f\"You worked as a {title} at {company}. \"\n                \"Can you walk me through a significant project there and your technical approach?\"\n            )\n\n    # 4. Project-based questions\n    for proj in candidate_profile.get(\"projects\", []):\n        name = proj.get(\"project_name\", \"a project\")\n        desc = proj.get(\"description\", \"\")\n        questions.append(\n            f\"Regarding your project '{name}', you mentioned: {desc} \"\n            \"What architecture did you choose and why?\"\n        )\n\n    # 5. Design questions\n    if \"Specific technologies proficiency\" in job_criteria or \"Technical Skills\" in job_criteria:\n        questions.append(\n            \"Design a simple microservice for a real-time chat application. \"\n            \"What components would you include and how would they interact?\"\n        )\n\n    # 6. Leadership / teamwork questions\n    if \"Leadership\" in job_criteria or \"Teamwork\" in job_criteria:\n        questions.append(\n            \"Tell me about a time you led or collaborated closely with a technical team. \"\n            \"How did you ensure effective communication and delivery?\"\n        )\n\n    # 7. Communication skills\n    if \"Communication skills\" in job_criteria:\n        questions.append(\n            \"How do you ensure clear and effective communication when explaining technical concepts \"\n            \"to non-technical stakeholders?\"\n        )\n\n    # 8. Adaptability\n    if \"Adaptability\" in job_criteria:\n        questions.append(\n            \"Tell me about a time you had to learn a new technology or process quickly. \"\n            \"How did you approach it and what was the outcome?\"\n        )\n\n    # Shuffle to mix question types\n    random.shuffle(questions)\n    return questions\n\ndef conduct_technical_interview(job_criteria, candidate_profile):\n    \"\"\"\n    Conducts the technical interview by generating questions and collecting responses.\n\n    Args:\n        job_criteria (list of str): Evaluation criteria.\n        candidate_profile (dict): Candidate details.\n\n    Returns:\n        tuple:\n            questions (list of str): Generated questions.\n            responses (list of str): Candidate's answers.\n    \"\"\"\n    questions = generate_technical_questions(job_criteria, candidate_profile)\n    responses = []\n\n    print(\"---- Technical Interview ----\")\n    for i, q in enumerate(questions, start=1):\n        print(f\"\\nQ{i}: {q}\")\n        ans = input(\"Your response: \").strip()\n        responses.append(ans)\n\n    print(\"\\nInterview complete. Responses collected.\")\n    return questions, responses\n\ndef technical_interview_module(job_description_criteria, candidate_resume):\n    \"\"\"\n    Conducts a technical interview based on job criteria and candidate profile.\n\n    Args:\n        job_description_criteria (dict): Contains 'job_description_evaluation_criteria' key.\n        candidate_resume (dict): Contains 'candidate_profile' key.\n\n    Returns:\n        tuple:\n            questions (list of str): Generated questions.\n            responses (list of str): Collected responses.\n    \"\"\"\n    job_criteria = job_description_criteria[\"job_description_evaluation_criteria\"]\n    candidate_profile = candidate_resume[\"candidate_profile\"]\n    return conduct_technical_interview(job_criteria, candidate_profile)\n\n# Example usage\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    job_description_criteria = {\n        \"job_description_evaluation_criteria\": [\n            \"Technical Skills\",\n            \"Problem-solving abilities\",\n            \"Communication skills\",\n            \"Experience\",\n            \"Teamwork\",\n            \"Leadership\",\n            \"Adaptability\",\n            \"Specific technologies proficiency\"\n        ]\n    }\n    candidate_resume = {\n        \"candidate_profile\": {\n            \"skills\": [\"Python\", \"Docker\", \"AWS\", \"Kubernetes\"],\n            \"work_experience\": [\n                {\"job_title\": \"DevOps Engineer\", \"company\": \"CloudCorp\"}\n            ],\n            \"projects\": [\n                {\n                    \"project_name\": \"Deployment Pipeline\",\n                    \"description\": \"Built CI/CD pipeline using Jenkins and Docker.\"\n                }\n            ]\n        }\n    }\n\n    qs, rs = technical_interview_module(job_description_criteria, candidate_resume)\n    # Save the questions and responses to a text file\n    with open(\"technical_interview_transcript.txt\", \"w\") as f:\n        f.write(\"Generated Questions:\\n\")\n        for q in qs:\n            f.write(f\"- {q}\\n\")\n        f.write(\"\\nCollected Responses:\\n\")\n        for r in rs:\n            f.write(f\"- {r}\\n\")\n\n    print(\"\\nGenerated Questions and Collected Responses saved to technical_interview_transcript.txt\")\n```"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 17:01:51,037", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task4: ```python\nimport smtplib\nfrom email.mime.text import MIMEText\nfrom email.mime.multipart import MIMEMultipart\n\nclass EmailNotification:\n    def __init__(self, sender_email, sender_password, smtp_server, smtp_port):\n        \"\"\"\n        Initializes the EmailNotification module.\n\n        Args:\n            sender_email (str): The email address of the sender.\n            sender_password (str): The password of the sender's email account.\n            smtp_server (str): The SMTP server address (e.g., 'smtp.gmail.com').\n            smtp_port (int): The SMTP port number (e.g., 587).\n        \"\"\"\n        self.sender_email = sender_email\n        self.sender_password = sender_password\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\n        self.smtp_port = smtp_port\n\n    def send_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body, is_html=False):\n        \"\"\"\n        Sends an email to the specified recipient.\n\n        Args:\n            recipient_email (str): The email address of the recipient.\n            subject (str): The subject of the email.\n            body (str): The body of the email.\n            is_html (bool): Indicates if the body is HTML formatted. Defaults to False.\n        \"\"\"\n        msg = MIMEMultipart()\n        msg['From'] = self.sender_email\n        msg['To'] = recipient_email\n        msg['Subject'] = subject\n\n        if is_html:\n            msg.attach(MIMEText(body, 'html'))\n        else:\n            msg.attach(MIMEText(body, 'plain'))\n\n        try:\n            server = smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.smtp_port)\n            server.starttls()  # Secure the connection\n            server.login(self.sender_email, self.sender_password)\n            server.sendmail(self.sender_email, recipient_email, msg.as_string())\n            server.quit()\n            print(f\"Email sent successfully to {recipient_email}\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error sending email: {e}\")\n\n    def send_interview_invitation(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, job_title, date_time, meeting_link):\n         \"\"\"\n         Sends an interview invitation email to the candidate.\n\n         Args:\n            recipient_email (str): The email address of the candidate.\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n            job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate is applying for.\n            date_time (str): The date and time of the interview.\n            meeting_link (str): The link to the online meeting.\n         \"\"\"\n\n         subject = f\"Interview Invitation for {job_title} at [Your Company]\"\n         body = f\"\"\"\n         Dear {candidate_name},\n\n         We are pleased to invite you to an interview for the {job_title} position at [Your Company].\n\n         Date and Time: {date_time}\n         Meeting Link: {meeting_link}\n\n         Please confirm your availability by replying to this email.\n\n         We look forward to speaking with you.\n\n         Sincerely,\n         [Your Name]\n         [Your Title]\n         [Your Company]\n         \"\"\"\n         self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\n\n    def send_interview_followup(self, recipient_email, candidate_name):\n        \"\"\"\n        Sends a follow-up email to the candidate after the interview.\n\n        Args:\n            recipient_email (str): The email address of the candidate.\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n        \"\"\"\n        subject = \"Following Up on Your Interview at [Your Company]\"\n        body = f\"\"\"\n        Dear {candidate_name},\n\n        Thank you for taking the time to interview with us for the [Job Title] position.\n\n        We appreciate you sharing your experience and qualifications with us.  We are currently reviewing all candidates and will be in touch soon with an update on your application.\n\n        In the meantime, please do not hesitate to reach out if you have any questions.\n\n        Sincerely,\n        [Your Name]\n        [Your Title]\n        [Your Company]\n        \"\"\"\n        self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\n\n    def send_rejection_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, job_title):\n        \"\"\"Sends a rejection email to a candidate.\n\n        Args:\n            recipient_email (str): The email address of the candidate.\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n            job_title (str): The job title the candidate applied for.\n        \"\"\"\n\n        subject = f\"Update on Your Application for {job_title} at [Your Company]\"\n        body = f\"\"\"\n        Dear {candidate_name},\n\n        Thank you for your interest in the {job_title} position at [Your Company] and for taking the time to interview with us.\n\n        After careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with other candidates whose qualifications and experience more closely align with the requirements of this role.\n\n        This was a difficult decision, as we were impressed with many aspects of your background. We wish you the best of luck in your job search.\n\n        Sincerely,\n        [Your Name]\n        [Your Title]\n        [Your Company]\n        \"\"\"\n        self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\n\n    def send_offer_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, job_title, salary, start_date):\n        \"\"\"Sends an offer email to a candidate.\n\n        Args:\n            recipient_email (str): The email address of the candidate.\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n            job_title (str): The job title for the offer.\n            salary (str): The salary being offered.\n            start_date (str): The start date for the position.\n        \"\"\"\n\n        subject = f\"Job Offer: {job_title} at [Your Company]\"\n        body = f\"\"\"\n        Dear {candidate_name},\n\n        We are pleased to offer you the position of {job_title} at [Your Company]!\n\n        We were very impressed with your qualifications and believe you would be a valuable asset to our team.\n\n        Your starting salary will be {salary} per year, and your start date will be {start_date}.\n\n        Please review the attached offer letter for more details. We would appreciate it if you could let us know your decision by [Date].\n\n        We are excited about the possibility of you joining our team!\n\n        Sincerely,\n        [Your Name]\n        [Your Title]\n        [Your Company]\n        \"\"\"\n        self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\n\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Example Usage (Replace with your actual credentials and information)\n    sender_email = \"your_email@gmail.com\"  # Replace with your email address\n    sender_password = \"your_password\"  # Replace with your email password (or app password)\n    smtp_server = \"smtp.gmail.com\"  # Or your SMTP server\n    smtp_port = 587  # Or your SMTP port\n\n    email_module = EmailNotification(sender_email, sender_password, smtp_server, smtp_port)\n\n    # Example 1: Send an interview invitation\n    recipient_email = \"candidate@example.com\"\n    candidate_name = \"John Doe\"\n    job_title = \"Software Engineer\"\n    date_time = \"October 27, 2023, 10:00 AM\"\n    meeting_link = \"https://meet.google.com/xyz\"\n    email_module.send_interview_invitation(recipient_email, candidate_name, job_title, date_time, meeting_link)\n\n    # Example 2: Send an interview follow-up\n    email_module.send_interview_followup(recipient_email, candidate_name)\n\n    # Example 3: Send a rejection email\n    email_module.send_rejection_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, job_title)\n\n    # Example 4: Send an offer email\n    email_module.send_offer_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, job_title, \"$120,000\", \"November 15, 2023\")\n```\n"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 17:01:51,037", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task5: ```text\n1. Analyze the job description to extract key requirements and evaluation criteria.\n2. Analyze the candidate's resume to identify relevant skills, experience, and projects.\n3. Use the job description criteria and candidate profile to generate technical interview questions using the `generate_technical_questions` function from the technical interview module.\n4. Conduct the technical interview by presenting the generated questions to the candidate and recording their responses using the `conduct_technical_interview` function.\n5. Save the interview transcript (questions and answers) to a text file.\n6. For each candidate response, use the `score_candidate_response` function to generate a score based on predefined criteria weights and keywords. The criteria weights and keywords should be aligned with the job description.\n7. Combine the interview transcript and the scored responses into a final evaluation report. The report should include the questions asked, the candidate's responses, the scores for each criterion, and the overall score.\n8. Rank the candidates based on their overall scores from the evaluation reports.\n9. Send emails to the candidates to inform them of the interview results. This step is external.\n```"}
